Business Brief -- Harleysville Group Inc.:
   Automobile Insurance Firm
   In New Jersey Is Approved
Harleysville Group's 1991 share of the earned premiums for
this business is estimated to be $17 million.
   Harleysville Group said the action would separate the New
Jersey personal automobile insurance business from the public
company, thus removing the uncertainty associated with the
automobile insurance environment in that state from
Harleysville Group's results.
   Harleysville Group is a Harleysville, Pa., regional
holding company for six property and casualty insurers whose
marketing territory encompasses the East Coast. Harleysville
Mutual is a principal stockholder of Harleysville Group,
owning 70% of the common.